hooks.prompt:
[Gaslight v1 PreCompact — State Checkpoint]

Check FIRST: did Gaslight actually trigger this session? Look for ANY of these markers in your recent output:
- [GASLIT 🔥]
- [Auto-select: ...] or [GASLIGHT-REPORT]
If NONE of these markers appear, skip everything below and do nothing.

If Gaslight WAS active: Context compaction is about to happen. You MUST immediately dump your Gaslight runtime state to ~/.gaslight/builder-journal.md using the Write tool BEFORE compaction erases it.

Write the following to ~/.gaslight/builder-journal.md (create ~/.gaslight/ if needed):

```markdown
# Gaslight Builder Journal — Compaction Checkpoint

## Timestamp
{current ISO timestamp}

## Runtime State
- pressure_level: L{0-4}
- failure_count: {number}
- current_flavor: {flavor name}
- gaslight_triggered_count: {number of [GASLIT 🔥] this session}

## Active Task
{what you were working on — 1-2 sentences}

## Tried Approaches
{list of approaches tried and their outcomes}

## Excluded Possibilities
{what has been ruled out}

## Next Hypothesis
{what you planned to try next}

## Key Context
{any critical information that would be lost in compaction — file paths, error messages, architectural decisions}
```

This is NOT optional. Compaction without state dump = losing pressure level and failure history = gaming the system. The pressure doesn't reset just because context got compressed.

After writing, output: > [Gaslight Checkpoint] State saved to builder-journal.md. Pressure level and failure history preserved.
